polimi.reds.broker.routing
Class GenericTable

java.lang.Object
  polimi.reds.broker.routing.GenericTable
All Implemented Interfaces:
SubscriptionTable
public class GenericTable
extends java.lang.Object
implements SubscriptionTable

A SubscriptionTable is used by the REDS broker to store information about the subscriptions (i.e., filters) it received from its neighbors. The GenericTable does not make any assumption about the format of filters and messages it can store and manage. It implements the SubscriptionTable interface by keeping a simple list of filters for each neighbor, i.e., the list of filters received from that neighbor through subscription messages, and by using extensively the method Message.match to determine the list of neighbors subscribed to a given message. As a consequence of this choice, it is not particularly efficient (but it is "generic", as its name suggests).

Field Detail

data

protected java.util.Map data
The Map that stores information about received subscriptions. In particular, neighbors are used as keys and values are the set of filters received by the corresponding neighbor.

getAllFilters

public java.util.Collection getAllFilters(NodeDescriptor n)
Description copied from interface: SubscriptionTable
Returns the collection of filters associated to the given neighbor into the table.
If there are no filters associated to the neighbor, the returned collection is empty, but not null.

Every call to this method returns a new collection object, so that it can be used without problems even if the subscription table is modified concurrently.

Specified by:
getAllFilters in interface SubscriptionTable
Parameters:
n - The neighbor whose subscriptions must be taken.
Returns:
The collection of filters associated to the given neighbor into the table.
